    "For this, the discriminator D is enforced to be Lipschitz continuous (Gulrajani et al. 2017).",
    "GP enables D to target the ‖D‖ Lip to 1.",
    "The ‖D‖ Lip is defined as Lipschitz con- tinuity as shown in Eq.",
    "(23) reproduced from Lee and Seok (2020).",
    "(23), ‖D‖ Lip denotes the left side of the equation."
